main event: A bright, meteor-like object was observed over Cedar Rapids, Iowa on July 6, 1966 at around 10:32 pm CDT.
interesting points: The object was observed for 4-5 seconds by multiple witnesses.
The object was described as bright and resembling a meteor or fireball.
The incident was investigated by Project Blue Book, the official U.S. Air Force investigation of UFOs.
The Flower and Cook Observatory at the University of Pennsylvania provided an analysis of the sighting.
The Air Force concluded that the object was a bright meteor or fireball, and not an unidentified flying object.
photographs: No photographs included in the report
